CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 12, 1952, pg. 6 reads: "Donate Food To Camp Achievement - Mrs. Alma Illery, far right, founder and guiding spirit of Camp Achievement, vacation spot for underprivileged youngsters, is shown as she prepares to transport a small portion of the entire grocery store of which was donated to Camp Achievement by Mrs. Emma L. Dukes and Albert (Bobby) Dukes, far left, Herron Avenue grocers, who quit business this week. John Easley aide Mrs. Illery in transferring the food. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Emma L. Dukes and Albert "Bobby" Dukes, left, and John Easley and Alma Illery, right, standing at edge of truck bed full of food donated by the Dukes to be transported to Camp Achievement
